Language: <F P=105> Russian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Byrkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 10 Jan -- The Azerbaijani Army resumed its 
offensive along the entire Karabakh front at 0700 [0400 GMT]. 
ITAR-TASS was told on the telephone by the Nagorno-Karabakh 
Republic defense army headquarters that the fighting is 
particularly heavy in the Mardakert Rayon of Nagorno-Karabakh. 
On Sunday evening the Azerbaijani Army lost over 50 men killed, 
two tanks, and an APC during its offensive near the village of 
Magadiz. Karabakh's losses amounted to three killed and five 
wounded. 
  According to reports received by 1300, the situation on all 
sectors of the front remains tense and battles are continuing. 

